1. Accessing the underlying buffer data using `buffer.data() + buffer.read_ptr()` to get the current readable data position
2. Using `buffer.size()` to get the amount of available data
3. Performing a linear search through the available data range
4. Returning the position relative to the current read pointer or `npos` if not found
