   - Creates a read-only buffer adaptor from the input span
   - Uses the same `hexi::prefixed_varint` adaptors to decode the compact encoding
   - The stream automatically handles the varint decoding for size fields

The `prefixed_varint` adaptor ensures that small values (both the size prefixes and the actual data) use fewer bytes, achieving the desired compact serialization.

